</score>|width=290|caption=Repeat sign with first and second endings}}When a repeat calls for a different ending, numbered brackets above the bars indicate which to play the first time ('''1.'''), which to play the second time ('''2.'''), and so on if necessary. These are called "first-time bars" and "second-time bars", or "first and second endings". They are also known as "[[wikt:volta#Italian|volta]] brackets" and have no limit to how many there can be.
